In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 2011 as National Wilderness Month in the United States. He highlights the importance of wilderness areas and their role in providing clean water, undisturbed land, wildlife, and healthy ecosystems. The president mentions that wilderness areas also contribute to local economies through tourism and recreation. He emphasizes the need to preserve these natural surroundings and mentions the America's Great Outdoors Initiative, which aims to advance a conservation agenda for the 21st century. The Obama Administration has expanded protected wilderness areas by 2 million acres. The president encourages Americans to visit and enjoy wilderness areas, learn about their history, and help protect them as national treasures.